        public int getFirstIUPACPos(java.lang.String seq)
        Get the first IUPAC position from a sequence.
        Parameters:
        seq - Sequence with IUPAC format.
        Returns:
        The first IUPAC position in the sequence. If no IUPAC in the sequence then return -1.

        Get flanking sequence.
        Parameters:
        seq - Sequence with IUPAC format.
        flank_len - Flanking sequence length.
        central_pos - The central position.

        Get the multiple sequences according to all dNTPs.
        Parameters:
        seq - Sequence with IUPAC format.
        dntps_list - dNTPs list in the sequence.
        dntps_index - The index of dNTPs list, the dntps_index must be set as 0.
        Returns:
        A sequence list according to all dNTPs.
